    I-perm-005 (#1199) slice 3: runner flip — KEEP+LABEL under PG_ALWAYS_RELEASE (annotate not reconcile)
    
    Production activation of the keep-and-label verb. In run_honest_sweep_r3.py's post-4-role
    report-reconciliation block, the verdict-vs-report step now branches: when `always_release_enabled()`
    (PG_ALWAYS_RELEASE, already slate-activated) the runner calls `annotate_report_against_verdicts`
    (KEEP each non-VERIFIED claim + append its confidence marker) instead of
    `reconcile_report_against_verdicts` (DELETE). Flag OFF -> the existing reconcile/delete path is
    byte-identical.
    
    The per-claim marker is deterministic from `claim_labeler.confidence_bucket`: a non-VERIFIED claim
    is `low` when it cites evidence (audit_map.evidence_ids non-empty) or `no-source-found` when it does
    not — NEVER `high` (the §-1.1 invariant). Writes the labeled report.md + a `claim_confidence.json`
    sidecar (claim_id -> verdict/severity/marker) + `manifest.report_annotation`. SAME fail-closed
    contract as the redactor: a present-but-unpinnable claim aborts (report_redaction_failed) rather than
    ship unlabeled.
    
    Control flow: the `elif always_release_enabled():` is inserted BEFORE the legacy reconcile `else:` in
    the existing `if not non-VERIFIED / report-absent / audit_map-absent` chain, so both paths still
    require the audit_map; the absent/no-op guards are unchanged.
    
    Smoke (offline, replicating the branch logic): an UNSUPPORTED claim is KEPT + carries `[confidence:
    low ...]`; the VERIFIED neighbor + its [N] marker are byte-identical (one marker total); a
    no-cited-evidence non-VERIFIED claim resolves to the `no grounded source` marker. Runner compiles.
    
    This makes I-perm-005's keep-and-label LIVE on the next always-release run. Remaining: the report
    render of claim_confidence into the UI chip (frontend) + activate PG_SPAN_RESOLVER in the slate.
    
